            "This hadith narrates that the Prophet Muhammad, peace be upon him, said, quoting Allah Almighty:   Allah has recorded the good and the evil deeds. Then He made it clear that whoever intends to do a good deed but does not do it, Allah will write it down as a complete good deed with Him. And if he intends to do it and actually does it, Allah will write it down as ten good deeds up to seven hundred times, or many more. And if he intends to do an evil deed but does not do it, Allah will write it down as a complete good deed with Him. And if he intends to do it and actually does it, Allah will write it down as one evil deed. This hadith emphasizes the importance of intentions in our actions. If we have good intentions and strive to do good deeds, Allah rewards us generously. Even if we are unable to fulfill our intentions, Allah still rewards us for the sincere intention. On the other hand, if we have evil intentions and act upon them, we are held accountable for our actions.",
